== Oku-no-in of Tamon-ji ==
[[File:Rokkohime shrine, Kobe 003.jpg|right|thumb|150px|Rokkō Hime Shrine]]
The Oku-no-in (inner sanctuary) is located along Mount Rokkō’s ridgeline near {{ill|Gyōgai-iwa|ja|仰臥岩|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gyōgai-iwa|qq=}}, {{ill|Un-ga-iwa|ja|雲ヶ岩|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Un-ga-iwa|qq=}}, and {{ill|Rokkō Hime Shrine|ja|六甲比命神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokkō Hime Shrine|qq=}} (dedicated to {{ill|Benzaiten|ja|弁財天|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Benzaiten|qq=}}). According to legend, Hōdō-sennin encountered {{ill|Vaiśravaṇa|ja|毘沙門天|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Vaiśravaṇa|qq=}} here, descending on purple clouds during his ascetic training.
